<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="473" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">653.116/123: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal (<persName type="from">Caldwell</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-18T18:00:00+00:00">October 18, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 18—2:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>22. Referring to the Legation’s despatch No. 783, January 4,
                                    1933.<note n="27" xml:id="d473fn27">Not printed.</note> I am
                                informed unofficially that decrees imposing discriminatory charges
                                have been revoked. Foreign Office advise that new decree on the
                                subject will be published within a few days.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>